Villic <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=1xtro1>1xtro1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#333333>(11/5/02 3:30:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=125.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: In my experience...</span><hr size=1> First group attempt was 1 mage 1 rogue 1 warr 1 cleric 1 enc 1 SK. We got owned 4 times I was oom by middle of last wave just trying to keep DPS up. The enc didn't seem very good and cleric didn't have cure des spell for the slow so I'm not sure how good this group was.<br>
<br>
Next group was 2 mages 1 rogue 1 warrior 1 enc 1 cleric. With this combo we owned it very easy.  We had 1 epic pet and 1 61 lvl pet with the new swords and belt. We put the 2 pets on one mob and melee would attack another.  About the time the axe guy got to the stairs we would banish a third mob to reset the guy. Then the melee guys would finish their mob and attack the 4th one. We would then need 1 or 2 DD to finish pet mob and the guy would reset again with last mob at 50% thier mob being done along with the pets.<br>
<br>
Mainly we would time the kills to the axe guy. This saved mana and made the trials very easy. I had 40m left for the last mob that dropped the marks. <br>
<br>
I would think as long as you have 2 DDers 1 rogue or 2 rogues one DDer your fine. I ranger with his AA is good too, but mage with a mod, and improve reclaim energy if pet is about to die has a slight edge over a wiz in this to keep up with the entire trial. I have seen 3 wizards in a group do well but they were 3 63 lvls with all the new spells and the whole group was from the top server guild, so not really a good example for us average folks.<br>
<br>
I have mastery 3, so I chain casted steel 2 or 3 times per mob and other mage cast 61 lvl bolt 1 time on the mobs that we wanted to burn.<br>
Xtro<br>
